"Abstract": "The world's best Call of Duty teams clash in the Major IV online qualifiers. From May 1-31, 2025, squads battle in \"Black Ops 6\" for crucial CDL points. Miami Heretics dominated, but rivals like FaZe and OpTic are ready for the main event. The stage is set for an epic showdown.",
"Approved": "no",
"Category": "esport",
"City": "Online",
"Core Text": "The Road to Glory: Call of Duty Major IV Qualifiers Heat Up!\n\nThe world of competitive Call of Duty is set for an explosive month of action as the online qualifiers for Major IV take center stage from the EFG Columbus Studio. From May 1st to May 31st, 2025, the top teams in the league will battle in a crucial online tournament to secure their seeding for the upcoming Major. This is where legends are forged and championship dreams are put to the ultimate test.\n\nThe path to victory is intense. The official schedule, running across the weekends of May 2-4, May 9-11, and May 16-18, will see twelve of the world's best teams collide in \"Call of Duty: Black Ops 6.\" The format is a grueling online, best-of-five series where every map counts. While no direct prize money is on the line for these qualifiers, teams are fighting for critical CDL Points, which determine their standing and path in the Major tournament. The \"Call of Duty League 2025 - Major 4 Qualifiers\" saw Miami Heretics dominate the field, finishing with a flawless 5-0 series record and an impressive 71% map win rate. Close behind, Atlanta FaZe secured a 4-1 record, while OpTic Texas and the Los Angeles Thieves rounded out the top four, both with 3-2 records. Information on a specific \"Challenger Elite III-IV\" tournament for this period was not available in the search results.\n\nAs the dust settles on the qualifiers, the battle lines are drawn for Major IV. With teams like the Miami Heretics showing incredible form and established powerhouses like OpTic and FaZe hungry for another title, the main event promises to be an unforgettable spectacle. The online arena has set the stage, but the war is far from over. Stay tuned as these elite squads prepare to clash in the next chapter of the Call of Duty League",
