"Schedule": "May 1-3, 6-10, 29-31",
"Short Text": "<div>\n<h4>The Road to Glory: Major IV Qualifiers Heat Up!</h4>\n<p>The competitive Call of Duty scene is buzzing as the online qualifiers for Major IV unfold throughout May 2025. From the EFG Columbus Studio, the world's elite teams are battling in 'Call of Duty: Black Ops 6' to secure crucial seeding for the main event. Over three intense weekends (May 2-4, 9-11, and 16-18), twelve squads face off in grueling best-of-five series. While there's no prize money, the stakes are immense, with vital CDL Points on the line that will shape the road to the championship. The Miami Heretics have emerged as a dominant force, concluding the qualifiers with a perfect 5-0 series record and an impressive 71% map win rate. Hot on their heels, Atlanta FaZe secured a 4-1 record, while OpTic Texas and the Los Angeles Thieves also locked in top spots. The stage is now set for an unforgettable Major IV, where these titans will clash for glory. The online qualifiers were just the beginning; the real war is yet to come.</p>\n</div>",
"Text": "<p><strong><em>The Road to Glory: Call of Duty Major IV Qualifiers Heat Up!</em></strong></p><p>The world of competitive Call of Duty is set for an <italic>explosive month of action</italic> as the online qualifiers for Major IV take center stage from the EFG Columbus Studio. From May 1st to May 31st, 2025, the top teams in the league will battle in a crucial online tournament to secure their seeding for the upcoming Major. This is where <strong>legends are forged</strong> and championship dreams are put to the ultimate test.</p><p>The path to victory is intense. The official schedule, running across the weekends of May 2-4, May 9-11, and May 16-18, will see twelve of the world's best teams collide in <italic>\"Call of Duty: Black Ops 6.\"</italic> The format is a grueling online, best-of-five series where every map counts. While no direct prize money is on the line for these qualifiers, teams are fighting for critical <strong>CDL Points</strong>, which determine their standing and path in the Major tournament. The \"Call of Duty League 2025 - Major 4 Qualifiers\" saw Miami Heretics dominate the field, finishing with a flawless 5-0 series record and an impressive 71% map win rate. Close behind, Atlanta FaZe secured a 4-1 record, while OpTic Texas and the Los Angeles Thieves rounded out the top four, both with 3-2 records. Information on a specific \"Challenger Elite III-IV\" tournament for this period was not available in the search results.</p><p>As the dust settles on the qualifiers, the battle lines are drawn for Major IV. With teams like the Miami Heretics showing incredible form and established powerhouses like <italic>OpTic and FaZe</italic> hungry for another title, the main event promises to be an <strong>unforgettable spectacle</strong>. The online arena has set the stage, but the war is far from over. Stay tuned as these elite squads prepare to clash in the next chapter of the Call of Duty League.</p>",
