"Abstract": "DreamHack returns to Atlanta, May 15-17, at the GWCC for a massive gaming festival. The event features top-tier esports tournaments, including IEM Counter-Strike and the Call of Duty League's Major III, uniting fans and pros for an unforgettable celebration of gaming culture.",
"Approved": "no",
"Category": "esport",
"City": "Atlanta",
"Core Text": "DreamHack Returns to Atlanta: The Ultimate Gaming Showdown\n\nGet ready, EFG community, because the world’s premier gaming lifestyle festival is making its triumphant return to Atlanta! DreamHack is set to take over the Georgia World Congress Center (GWCC) for a weekend of unparalleled esports action, community celebration, and unforgettable moments. The city will become the epicenter of the gaming universe, where legends are born and fans witness history in the making.\n\nMark your calendars for May 15-17, as DreamHack Atlanta kicks off with a showcase of elite-level esports. The main stage will be dominated by two of the biggest titles in competitive gaming. For the first time, IEM will bring its world-class Counter-Strike tournament to Atlanta, featuring 16 of the planet's best teams battling for supremacy. Alongside them, the Call of Duty League takes center stage with CDL Major III, a high-stakes Pro-Am where 12 franchise teams will clash with 4 hungry Challengers rosters. The action continues with the Call of Duty: Warzone Resurgence Series taking place from May 16-17. While specific prize pools for the IEM and CDL May events are yet to be announced, the festival's full 2025 esports program promises a staggering combined prize pool of $6.6 million. The larger schedule includes the SNK World Championship ($4.1 million circuit prize), the $1 million MARVEL RIVALS Ignite Grand Finals, the $700,000 Clash of Clans World Championship, the $500,000 Clash Royale League World Finals, and the $152,000 EA SPORTS FC Pro Open Global Qualifier, ensuring a monumental year for competition in Atlanta.\n\nThis is more than just a tournament; it's a celebration of everything we love about gaming. From the roar of the crowd during a clutch play to the shared passion on the expo floor, DreamHack Atlanta 2025 is the place to be. Whether you're a die-hard competitor or a casual fan, prepare for a gaming experience like no other. The hype is real—we'll see you at the GWCC",
