"Abstract": "While hopes for an IEM Atlanta event in 2025 are unmet, 2026 is set to be a landmark year. From May 15-17, DreamHack Atlanta will host the prestigious IEM tournament, featuring elite Counter-Strike 2 and Call of Duty League action, positioning it as a can't-miss North American esports event.",
"Approved": "no",
"Category": "esport",
"City": "Atlanta",
"Core Text": "Atlanta's Esports Future: IEM Confirmed for 2026\n\nWhile the esports community has been anticipating news regarding a potential Intel® Extreme Masters (IEM) event in Atlanta for 2025, official web searches have not returned any information for a tournament on the requested dates of May 11-17, 2025. Currently, details for an event in that timeframe are unavailable.\n\nHowever, the competitive gaming scene is set to explode in Georgia the following year. ESL has confirmed that IEM will make its grand debut in Atlanta from May 15-17, 2026, at the Georgia World Congress Center. This massive event will be a cornerstone of the DreamHack Atlanta festival, which saw nearly 40,000 attendees in its previous iteration. The festival will feature the world's elite in Counter-Strike 2, with 16 top-tier teams battling for a share of a massive $1,050,000 prize pool and a crucial victory in the race for the ESL Grand Slam V. Alongside the CS2 action, the event will host the Call of Duty League Major III, where all 12 professional teams will compete for vital circuit points. Further tournaments, including a potential DreamHack Open for Halo, have also been indicated, promising a packed schedule for attendees.\n\nGet ready, EFG community! While 2025 remains unconfirmed, all eyes are now on 2026. The combination of IEM's prestige and a CDL Major positions DreamHack Atlanta as one of the most anticipated North American esports events of the year. The road to Atlanta has begun",
"Date From": "2025-05-11T12:00:00.000Z",
