"Schedule": "May 11 -17",
"Short Text": "<div>\n<h2>Atlanta's Esports Scene Sets Sights on a Massive 2026</h2>\n<p>While anticipation for an Intel® Extreme Masters (IEM) event in Atlanta for 2025 has been met with silence, the city's esports future is set to explode in 2026. ESL has confirmed that IEM will make its grand debut in Atlanta from May 15-17, 2026, at the Georgia World Congress Center, as a cornerstone of the DreamHack Atlanta festival.</p><p>This massive event, which previously drew nearly 40,000 attendees, will feature the world's Counter-Strike 2 elite, with 16 top-tier teams battling for a $1,050,000 prize pool and a key victory in the ESL Grand Slam V race. Alongside the CS2 action, the festival will host the Call of Duty League Major III, where all 12 professional teams will compete for vital circuit points. With other tournaments also indicated, DreamHack Atlanta is positioned to be one of North America's most anticipated esports events. While 2025 is unconfirmed, all eyes are now on 2026!</p>\n</div>",
"Text": "<p><strong>Atlanta's Esports Future: IEM Confirmed for 2026</strong></p><p>While the esports community has been anticipating news regarding a potential <italic>Intel® Extreme Masters (IEM)</italic> event in Atlanta for 2025, official web searches have not returned any information for a tournament on the requested dates of <italic>May 11-17, 2025</italic>. Currently, details for an event in that timeframe are unavailable.</p><p>However, the competitive gaming scene is set to explode in Georgia the following year. ESL has confirmed that <strong>IEM</strong> will make its grand debut in Atlanta from <strong>May 15-17, 2026</strong>, at the <strong>Georgia World Congress Center</strong>. This massive event will be a cornerstone of the <strong>DreamHack Atlanta</strong> festival, which saw nearly 40,000 attendees in its previous iteration. The festival will feature the world's elite in <strong>Counter-Strike 2</strong>, with 16 top-tier teams battling for a share of a massive <strong>$1,050,000 prize pool</strong> and a crucial victory in the race for the <italic>ESL Grand Slam V</italic>. Alongside the CS2 action, the event will host the <strong>Call of Duty League Major III</strong>, where all 12 professional teams will compete for vital circuit points. Further tournaments, including a potential <italic>DreamHack Open for Halo</italic>, have also been indicated, promising a packed schedule for attendees.</p><p><italic>Get ready, EFG community!</italic> While 2025 remains unconfirmed, all eyes are now on 2026. The combination of IEM's prestige and a CDL Major positions <strong>DreamHack Atlanta</strong> as one of the most anticipated North American esports events of the year. The road to Atlanta has begun.</p>",
