"Approved": "no",
"Category": "esport",
"City": "Online",
"Core Text": "Call of Duty: Major II Qualifier & Challenger Elite II Heats Up\n\nThe battlegrounds of Call of Duty are set to ignite as the Major II Qualifier and Challenger Elite II take center stage. From March 1st to March 22nd, 2025, the world's best will clash in a high-stakes online competition broadcast from the EFG Columbus Studio. This event promises to be a crucible of skill, strategy, and raw talent, as teams vie for glory and a significant prize pool.\n\nThe action will be relentless, with a detailed schedule spanning the month. The main event, the CDC North America 2025 Elite Stage 2, will be a focal point of the competition. The tournament series will be played on Black Ops 6, featuring a 4v4 format with game types like Hardpoint, Search & Destroy, and Control. The total prize pool for the CDC North America 2025 Elite season is a staggering $216,000, with $72,000 up for grabs in Stage 2 alone. Mark your calendars for the key dates: Mar 1, 4-8, 11-15, 18-22. The CDC North America 2025 Elite Stage 2 Playoffs, with a prize of $2,000 for 7th-8th place, will unfold on March 13th. Preceding this, the Elite Stage 2 will see teams battle on March 4th. The journey to this stage was forged in the fire of the Elite Stage 2 Qualifier on February 23rd. Another key event to watch is the CDC North America 2025 Cup #8 on March 16th. With a history of over $6 million awarded in prize money for Call of Duty: Modern Warfare II tournaments, the stakes are higher than ever.\n\nAs the community buzzes with anticipation, all eyes are on the players. The world of competitive Call of Duty has seen legends rise and empires fall, with top players earning hundreds of thousands of dollars in prize money. This tournament will be another chapter in that storied history. Get ready for a month of unparalleled esports action. The strategies will be deep, the clutches will be legendary, and the victors will be immortalized. Don't miss a moment of the Call of Duty: Major II Qualifier & C