"Abstract": "After three successful years, IEM has shockingly cancelled its 2025 Rio de Janeiro event, leaving Brazil off the next ESL Counter-Strike tour. The news has stunned the passionate fanbase, though discussions for a potential return to the city in 2026 offer a glimmer of hope for the future.",
"Approved": "no",
"Category": "esport",
"City": "Rio",
"Core Text": "IEM Rio 2025 Cancelled, Brazil Left Off Next Year's ESL Tour\n\nIn a surprising turn of events for the global Counter-Strike community, Intel Extreme Masters (IEM) will not be returning to Rio de Janeiro in 2025. After three consecutive years of electrifying tournaments that captured the hearts of fans worldwide, ESL has made the decision to exclude the vibrant Brazilian city from its schedule for the upcoming season.\n\nThe news, confirmed by Dust2 Brasil, comes as a shock to many, especially given the unparalleled passion and success of the previous IEM Rio events. While the city itself had expressed interest in continuing the partnership, current plans from ESL show a 2025 roadmap without a stop in Brazil. Fans who were eagerly anticipating the event, tentatively scheduled from April 13th to April 19th, will unfortunately have to wait longer for the return of a premier ESL CS2 tournament to their home soil.\n\nBased on the information available, no official list of games, prize pools, or specific tournament formats for a 2025 Rio event can be provided as the event is not scheduled to take place. Discussions are reportedly underway for a potential return to Rio in 2026, offering a glimmer of hope to the dedicated Brazilian fanbase. For now, the community is left to reminisce about the legendary moments from past years as they await future announcements.",
"Date From": "2025-04-13T12:00:00.000Z",
