"Core Text": "DreamHack Atlanta 2025: A Halloween Gaming Spectacle\n\nGet ready for an electrifying Halloween weekend as DreamHack, the world's premier gaming lifestyle festival, makes its grand return to Atlanta, GA. This year, the event promises to be bigger and more vibrant than ever, transforming the Georgia World Congress Center into the ultimate haunted playground for gamers and esports fanatics.\n\nMark your calendars for an unforgettable three-day experience from October 31st to November 2nd, 2025. DreamHack Atlanta is set to be a landmark event, merging top-tier competitive gaming with a massive Halloween celebration, including America's largest costume contest with a $20,000 prize pool. The festival floor will be a hub of activity, from trick-or-treating and spooky quests to a massive LAN party and an expansive indie playground.\n\nThe competitive pulse of the event will feature over 20 tournaments, including seven world championship titles, with a staggering combined prize pool of nearly $6.6 million. The action kicks off from Oct 31- Nov 2 with a schedule packed with high-stakes clashes. The fighting game community will witness history with the SNK World Championship, boasting a colossal $4.1 million prize pool across titles like *Fatal Fury: City of the Wolves* ($2.5M), *King of Fighters XV* ($1M), and *Samurai Shodown* ($500k). The hype continues with the $1 million *MARVEL RIVALS: Ignite Grand Finals*. Mobile gaming titans will collide in the *Clash of Clans World Championship Finals* ($700k) and the *Clash Royale League World Finals* ($500k). Other major competitions include the *EA Sports FC 26: FC Pro Open* ($152k), the *CFB26 DreamHack Challenge* ($25k), and the *Rainbow 6 Siege X Atlanta* tournament ($10k). Furthermore, the *DreamHack Knockout* for CS2 will offer $10,000 and a coveted spot in ESL Pro League Season 23, solidifying DreamHack's role as a proving ground for champions.\n\nDreamHack Atlanta 2025 is more than just a series of tournaments; it's a celebration of gaming culture in all its forms. With a record-breaking attendance of over 52,000 visitors from 59 countries in the previous year, the festival is the definitive gathering for the gaming community. Whether you're a competitive player aiming for glory, a dedicated fan eager to watch the pros, a cosplayer ready to showcase your craft, or simply looking to connect with fellow gamers, Atlanta is the place to be. Prepare for a weekend of non-stop action, community spirit, and unforgettable memories.",
